<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>Inline Review Test Page</title>
    <style>
      body {
        font-family: system-ui, sans-serif;
        max-width: 640px;
        margin: 2rem auto;
        padding: 0 1rem;
        line-height: 1.6;
        color: #333;
      }
      h1 { color: #1a1a2e; }
      h2 { color: #16213e; margin-top: 2rem; }
      .card {
        border: 1px solid #ddd;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 1rem;
        margin: 1rem 0;
        background: #fafafa;
      }
      button {
        padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
        border: 1px solid #ccc;
        border-radius: 4px;
        background: #fff;
        cursor: pointer;
      }
      a { color: #e94560; }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <nav><a href="/about">Go to About Page &rarr;</a></nav>

    <h1>Inline Review Test Page</h1>

    <p>
      This is a minimal page for testing the review-loop overlay.
      Select any text on this page and add an annotation, or Alt+click an
      element to annotate it directly.
    </p>

    <h2>Text Selection Test</h2>
    <p>
      Here is a paragraph with enough content to test text selection. You
      should be able to highlight a portion of this sentence and create a
      text annotation with a note describing what needs to change.
    </p>
    <p>
      A second paragraph provides additional text for testing multi-paragraph
      selection and verifying that highlights render correctly across
      different DOM nodes.
    </p>

    <h2>Element Annotation Test</h2>
    <div class="card" id="sample-card">
      <h3>Sample Card</h3>
      <p>Alt+click this card to annotate the entire element.</p>
    </div>

    <button id="sample-button">Example Button</button>
    <a href="#" id="sample-link">Example Link</a>

    <h2>Longer Content</h2>
    <p>
      This section exists so you can test scroll-based behaviours. When you
      scroll away from a popup, it should dismiss after a short threshold.
      Keep scrolling to verify.
    </p>
    <p>
      Final paragraph. Use the floating action button in the bottom-right
      corner to open the annotations panel and review everything you have
      added during this session.
    </p>
  </body>
</html>
